item.title: A Test Lecture
item.description: Learning Objectives Learning one thing Learn another thing A final thing to learn Principles of Title Registration Curtain Mirror Assurance Curtain: Registered owner is by definition owner of title (in absence of fraud on owner's part) Mirror: Once registered, title holder has priority over all prior unregistered interests. Registry reflects all valid interests. Assurance (Net): If owner suffers loss because of error or fraud, compensation available.
